OL,3,CTrain driver fell asleep before
OL,4,Ccrashing into buffers
OL,6,FA train hit the buffers at one of the
OL,7,FUK's busiest railway stations because
OL,8,Fthe driver fell asleep, an
OL,9,Finvestigation has found.
OL,11,FThe low-speed incident happened at
OL,12,FLondon Bridge station at 3.45pm on
OL,13,FDecember 13 last year.
OL,15,FA report by the Rail Accident
OL,16,FInvestigation Branch (RAIB), who did
OL,17,Fnot name the Southern Railway driver,
OL,18,Fsaid he "experienced a microsleep due
OL,19,Fto fatigue".
