OL,3,CTrain driver fell asleep before
OL,4,Ccrashing into buffers
OL,6,FHe got less than his normal amount of
OL,7,Fsleep the night before the accident
OL,8,Fbecause of childcare arrangements, the
OL,9,Finvestigation found.
OL,11,FThe RAIB also noted he had been
OL,12,Fworking on many of his scheduled rest
OL,13,Fdays, increasing his risk of fatigue.
OL,15,FThe train was travelling at 2.3mph
OL,16,Fwhen it hit the buffers on arrival at
OL,17,Fplatform 12.
OL,19,FThere was minor damage to the train
OL,20,Fand railway infrastructure, but no
OL,21,Freported injuries.
