OL,6,FAnalysis of an onboard data recorder
OL,7,Fshows the train was travelling at
OL,8,F13.3mph when it entered the platform,
OL,9,Fand gradually reduced its speed.
OL,11,FThe driver applied the emergency brake
OL,12,Fwhen the train was three-and-a-half
OL,13,Fmetres from the buffers, but it was
OL,14,Ftoo late to prevent a collision.
OL,16,FHe normally stayed in bed until 9am
OL,17,Fbefore an early afternoon start for
OL,18,Fwork, but had to get up at 7.30am on
OL,19,Fthe morning of the crash because of
OL,20,F"unexpected changes in childcare
OL,21,Farrangements at home", the RAIB said.
