OL,3,CTrain driver fell asleep before
OL,4,Ccrashing into buffers
OL,6,FInvestigators noted the driver
OL,7,Frecalled that when the train stopped
OL,8,Fat Crystal Palace station 26 minutes
OL,9,Fbefore the incident, he began to "feel
OL,10,Ftried" and recognised "the need to
OL,11,Ffocus and remain alert".
OL,13,FThe report added: "Although aware that
OL,14,Fthey were feeling tired, the driver
OL,15,Ffelt able to continue the journey."
OL,17,FHe was scheduled to have 12 rest days
OL,18,Fin the 22 days preceding the accident,
OL,19,Fbut worked on nine of these.
