OL,3,CTrain driver fell asleep before
OL,4,Ccrashing into buffers
OL,6,FMany train operators rely on drivers
OL,7,Fvolunteering for paid extra shifts to
OL,8,Frun timetabled services.
OL,10,FThe investigation also noted that none
OL,11,Fof the protection systems fitted to
OL,12,Fthe train prevented it hitting the
OL,13,Fbuffers, as it was travelling below
OL,14,Fthe minimum speed they intervene at.
OL,16,FOther safety systems could no detect
OL,17,Fthe "short loss of driver alertness
OL,18,Fthat occurred", the report found.
